## ONE-TIME SETUP (do this once)

### A — Deploy Flask Backend to Render.com

1. Go to https://render.com and sign up (free, no credit card needed)

2. Click "New +" → "Web Service"

3. Connect your GitHub repo → select this repo

4. Configure:
   - Name: interior-ai-backend
   - Root Directory: backend
   - Build Command: pip install -r requirements.txt
   - Start Command: gunicorn -w 2 -b 0.0.0.0:$PORT app:app
   - Plan: Free

5. Add Environment Variables (click "Add Environment Variable"):
   - ALLOWED_ORIGINS = https://your-app.vercel.app
     (replace with your actual Vercel URL)

6. Click "Create Web Service"
   → Wait ~3 minutes for first deploy
   → You get a URL like: https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com
   → Save this URL — you will use it forever

### B — Add Backend URL to Vercel

1. Go to vercel.com → your project → Settings → Environment Variables

2. Add:
   - Name:  REACT_APP_API_URL
   - Value: https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com
     (use YOUR actual Render URL)

3. Click Save → go to Deployments → click "Redeploy" on latest deployment

4. Done. Your Vercel frontend now talks to your Render backend.

### C — Update Your Startup Guide (Step 4)

The ONLY change to your existing Colab workflow:
  OLD: Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://localhost:5000/set-colab-url" ...
  NEW: Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com/set-colab-url" ...

