## DAILY STARTUP (when you want to use AI features)

Steps 1 and 2 (local Flask + local React) are NO LONGER NEEDED.
The app runs on Vercel + Render automatically.

You only need to do this when you want AI generation:

**Step 1 — Open Google Colab and run all cells in order:**

1.  Imports
2.  Cache directory
3.  Load ControlNet
4.  Load Stable Diffusion
5.  Load Inpainting pipeline
6.  Load YOLOv8
7.  Load SAM
8.  Helper functions
9.  Style prompts
10. generate_style function
11. detect_objects function
12. edit_object function
13. Flask API + ngrok cell
14. ngrok auth token cell

Wait for the ngrok URL to print (example: https://xyz-abc.ngrok-free.app)

---

**Step 2 — Register the Colab URL with your Render backend:**

Windows PowerShell:
```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest `
  -Uri "https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com/set-colab-url" `
  -Method POST `
  -ContentType "application/json" `
  -Body '{"url": "https://YOUR-NGROK-URL.ngrok-free.app"}'
```

Mac/Linux terminal:
```bash
curl -X POST https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com/set-colab-url \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"url": "https://YOUR-NGROK-URL.ngrok-free.app"}'
```

Replace YOUR-NGROK-URL with the actual URL from Colab.

---

**Step 3 — Verify connection:**

```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://interior-ai-backend.onrender.com/health" -Method GET
```

You should see:
  "colab_connected": true
  "mode": "colab"

---

**Step 4 — Open the app:**

Go to your Vercel URL (e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app)
The app is now live for everyone on any device.

